{\fs14}你现在还有什么要说，谦卑的贝罗斯先生？{\r}
{\fs12\1c&H00FFFF&\b0\i1}What do you say now, Mr. Humble Bellows?{\r}

104
00:12:41,477 --> 00:12:44,272
{\fs14}你谦卑的仆人会相信的...{\r}
{\fs12\1c&H00FFFF&\b0\i1}Thy humble servant will believe it...{\r}

105
00:12:44,355 --> 00:12:46,649
{\fs14}当你谦卑的仆人看得到时{\r}
{\fs12\1c&H00FFFF&\b0\i1}when thy humble servant sees it.{\r}

106
00:12:47,483 --> 00:12:49,861
{\fs14}我想我们成交了，船长{\r}
{\fs12\1c&H00FFFF&\b0\i1}I take it we have a deal, Captain.{\r}

107
00:13:21,810 --> 00:13:24,729
{\fs14}这次换船，船长，让人很不愉快{\r}
{\fs12\1c&H00FFFF&\b0\i1}This change of ship, Captain, most uncomfortable.{\r}

108
00:13:24,855 --> 00:13:28,108
{\fs14}我的人不会转移货物，这种活太实在了{\r}
{\fs12\1c&H00FFFF&\b0\i1}My men won't transfer cargo. Too much like honest work.{\r}

109
00:13:28,191 --> 00:13:31,653
{\fs14}瓦洛船长，你的人只给我留了艏斜帆和上桅帆{\r}
{\fs12\1c&H00FFFF&\b0\i1}Captain Vallo, your men have only left me headsail and topsail.{\r}

110
00:13:31,737 --> 00:13:34,406
{\fs14}它们早晚会把你送到眼镜蛇岛的{\r}
{\fs12\1c&H00FFFF&\b0\i1}They're enough to get you to Cobra sooner or later.{\r}

111
00:13:34,489 --> 00:13:36,658
{\fs14}我的船比这艘驳船快{\r}
{\fs12\1c&H00FFFF&\b0\i1}My ship is faster than this barge.{\r}

112
00:13:36,700 --> 00:13:40,370
{\fs14}我不能让你在我完成与埃尔·利布勒的交易之前到港{\r}
{\fs12\1c&H00FFFF&\b0\i1}I don't want you making port before I've got El Libre ready for delivery...{\r}

113
00:13:40,454 --> 00:13:42,497
{\fs14}或者在我背后开枪{\r}
{\fs12\1c&H00FFFF&\b0\i1}or putting a shot in my backside.{\r}

114
00:13:42,581 --> 00:13:46,043
{\fs14}希望埃尔·利布勒不像你这么小心，船长{\r}
{\fs12\1c&H00FFFF&\b0\i1}I hope El Libre is not as careful as you are, Captain.{\r}

115
00:13:57,763 --> 00:13:59,765
{\fs14}放开舵！{\r}
{\fs12\1c&H00FFFF&\b0\i1}Cast off helm!{\r}

116
00:14:01,684 --> 00:14:03,852
{\fs14}放开船尾！{\r}
{\fs12\1c&H00FFFF&\b0\i1}Cast off stern!{\r}

117
00:14:05,896 --> 00:14:10,025
{\fs14}- 贝洛斯先生，起航！  - 是，是的，先生！{\r}
{\fs12\1c&H00FFFF&\b0\i1}- Mr. Bellows, make sail!
- Aye, aye, sir!{\r}

118
00:14:35,259 --> 00:14:37,053
{\fs14}拉起来，满帆{\r}
{\fs12\1c&H00FFFF&\b0\i1}Haul up, full and by.{\r}

119
00:14:37,512 --> 00:14:41,057
{\fs14}北北东，我们要去眼镜蛇岛{\r}
{\fs12\1c&H00FFFF&\b0\i1}Nor' nor' east. We're heading for the Isle of Cobra.{\r}

120
00:14:41,641 --> 00:14:43,726
{\fs14}快点，你们这些笨蛋，动起来！{\r}
{\fs12\1c&H00FFFF&\b0\i1}Come on, you lubbers, move!{\r}

121
00:15:20,055 --> 00:15:22,933
{\fs14}听，听！{\r}
{\fs12\1c&H00FFFF&\b0\i1}Hear ye, hear ye!{\r}

122
00:15:23,183 --> 00:15:26,353
{\fs14}国王的船现在抛锚了...{\r}
{\fs12\1c&H00FFFF&\b0\i1}The King's vessel is now at anchor...{\r}

123
00:15:26,436 --> 00:15:29,898
{\fs14}在眼镜蛇港，格鲁达男爵乘坐此船{\r}
{\fs12\1c&H00FFFF&\b0\i1}in the port of Cobra with Baron Gruda aboard.{\r}

124
00:15:29,981 --> 00:15:34,778
{\fs14}任何示威都将被视为叛国罪{\r}
{\fs12\1c&H00FFFF&\b0\i1}Any demonstration will be regarded as high treason.{\r}

125
00:15:36,655 --> 00:15:38,782
{\fs14}人们看起来很安静，不是吗？{\r}
{\fs12\1c&H00FFFF&\b0\i1}The people seem very quiet, don't they?{\r}

126
00:15:38,865 --> 00:15:42,411
{\fs14}我认为他们根本没打算向格鲁达男爵示威抗议{\r}
{\fs12\1c&H00FFFF&\b0\i1}I don't think they intend to demonstrate against Baron Gruda after all.{\r}

127
00:15:42,494 --> 00:15:45,163
{\fs14}- 显然没有，总督   - 真遗憾{\r}
{\fs12\1c&H00FFFF&\b0\i1}- Apparently not, Governor.
- What a pity.{\r}

128
00:15:45,247 --> 00:15:47,833
{\fs14}我们的军队本可以像割小麦一样把他们砍倒{\r}
{\fs12\1c&H00FFFF&\b0\i1}Our troops could've cut them down like wheat.{\r}

129
00:15:48,250 --> 00:15:50,669
{\fs14}我们不能按照一般原则杀一些吗？{\r}
{\fs12\1c&H00FFFF&\b0\i1}Couldn't we shoot a few on general principles?{\r}

130
00:15:50,711 --> 00:15:52,129
{\fs14}这样也许能给男爵留下好印象{\r}
{\fs12\1c&H00FFFF&\b0\i1}Might impress the Baron.{\r}

131
00:15:52,171 --> 00:15:54,548
{\fs14}也有可能他会觉得你只是在惹麻烦{\r}
{\fs12\1c&H00FFFF&\b0\i1}He might feel you are merely provoking trouble.{\r}

132
00:15:54,631 --> 00:15:57,885
{\fs14}真令人恼火，向格鲁达男爵敬礼{\r}
{\fs12\1c&H00FFFF&\b0\i1}Most exasperating. Fire the salute to Baron Gruda.{\r}

133
00:16:00,679 --> 00:16:02,014
{\fs14}注意！{\r}
{\fs12\1c&H00FFFF&\b0\i1}Attention!{\r}

134
00:16:14,610 --> 00:16:18,823
{\fs14}给句话，我去给那些背刺者猛烈一击{\r}
{\fs12\1c&H00FFFF&\b0\i1}Give the word and I'll dose those backstabbers with a broadside.{\r}

135
00:16:19,198 --> 00:16:21,492
{\fs14}他们不是在向我们开火，你这个白痴{\r}
{\fs12\1c&H00FFFF&\b0\i1}They're not firing at us, you powder-brained ape.{\r}

136
00:16:21,575 --> 00:16:25,788
{\fs14}他们对我们放礼炮15响，因为我们悬挂的是格鲁达的旗帜{\r}
{\fs12\1c&H00FFFF&\b0\i1}They're giving us a 15-gun salute. We're flying the flag of Gruda.{\r}

137
00:16:25,871 --> 00:16:29,041
{\fs14}斯莱米，把旗子拿出来，把我给你的那封信拿出来{\r}
{\fs12\1c&H00FFFF&\b0\i1}Slimey, bring out the flags and run up that message I gave you.{\r}

138
00:16:29,875 --> 00:16:32,503
{\fs14}还有，斯莱米，代我向总督致意{\r}
{\fs12\1c&H00FFFF&\b0\i1}And, Slimey, give the Governor my compliments.{\r}

139
00:16:32,586 --> 00:16:34,130
{\fs14}红海盗的致意？{\r}
{\fs12\1c&H00FFFF&\b0\i1}The Crimson Pirate's?{\r}

140
00:16:34,213 --> 00:16:36,674
{\fs14}不，你这个牡蛎头，是格鲁达男爵的致意{\r}
{\fs12\1c&H00FFFF&\b0\i1}No, you oyster-head, Baron Gruda's.{\r}

141
00:16:37,425 --> 00:16:41,053
{\fs14}贝洛斯先生，让剩下的喽啰留在甲板下面{\r}
{\fs12\1c&H00FFFF&\b0\i1}Mr. Bellows, keep the rest of these half-masted monkeys below deck.{\r}

142
00:16:41,137 --> 00:16:42,430
{\fs14}是，是的，船长{\r}
{\fs12\1c&H00FFFF&\b0\i1}Aye, aye, Skipper.{\r}

143
00:16:42,513 --> 00:16:45,558
{\fs14}小心点，伙计们，我今晚会和埃尔·利布勒一起回来{\r}
{\fs12\1c&H00FFFF&\b0\i1}Keep a sharp lookout, lads. I'll be back with El Libre tonight.{\r}

144
00:16:45,641 --> 00:16:47,143
{\fs14}我们走，奥约{\r}
{\fs12\1c&H00FFFF&\b0\i1}Let's go, Ojo.{\r}

145
00:16:54,400 --> 00:16:58,696
{\fs14}那里有一个好海盗，像卖鱼小贩一样贩卖他的货{\r}
{\fs12\1c&H00FFFF&\b0\i1}There goes a good pirate, to sell his wares like a fish peddler.{\r}

146
00:16:59,238 --> 00:17:01,699
{\fs14}当然，这并不意味着对船长的不尊重{\r}
{\fs12\1c&H00FFFF&\b0\i1}Meaning no disrespect to the Skipper, of course.{\r}

147
00:17:01,783 --> 00:17:03,576
{\fs14}我们的脑袋都有悬赏...{\r}
{\fs12\1c&H00FFFF&\b0\i1}Us with a price on our heads...{\r}

148
00:17:03,660 --> 00:17:07,872
{\fs14}像鸭子一样藏在国王陛下的某个港口{\r}
{\fs12\1c&H00FFFF&\b0\i1}holed, too, in one of His Majesty's ports like sitting ducks.{\r}

149
00:17:08,623 --> 00:17:13,044
{\fs14}但如果船长再拉我们一把，我们就会成有金蛋的鸭子{\r}
{\fs12\1c&H00FFFF&\b0\i1}But if the Skipper pulls us through again, we'd be the ducks with the golden eggs.{\r}

150
00:17:13,086 --> 00:17:16,589
{\fs14}你想的是母鹅，原谅我的纠正，毒保罗{\r}
{\fs12\1c&H00FFFF&\b0\i1}You're thinking of geese, if you'll pardon the correction, Poison Paul.{\r}

151
00:17:17,048 --> 00:17:19,926
{\fs14}雁行之鹅{\r}
{\fs12\1c&H00FFFF&\b0\i1}Geese on a wild-goose chase.{\r}

152
00:17:31,271 --> 00:17:32,772
{\fs14}他们的旗语怎么说，约瑟夫？{\r}
{\fs12\1c&H00FFFF&\b0\i1}What do they say, Joseph?{\r}

153
00:17:32,814 --> 00:17:36,151
{\fs14}他们在船上发现了瘟疫，他们正在隔离自己...{\r}
{\fs12\1c&H00FFFF&\b0\i1}They've got the plague onboard, and they're quarantining themselves...{\r}

154
00:17:36,234 --> 00:17:38,278
{\fs14}直到染病者被杀死或治愈{\r}
{\fs12\1c&H00FFFF&\b0\i1}until the victims are killed or cured.{\r}

155
00:17:39,696 --> 00:17:42,491
{\fs14}我们必须向格鲁达男爵表示深切哀悼{\r}
{\fs12\1c&H00FFFF&\b0\i1}We must signal my profound condolences to Baron Gruda.{\r}

156
00:17:42,574 --> 00:17:45,452
{\fs14}- 很好，总督   - 也许这是最好的，约瑟夫{\r}
{\fs12\1c&H00FFFF&\b0\i1}- Very well, Governor.
- Maybe it's all for the best, Joseph.{\r}

157
00:17:45,494 --> 00:17:47,871
{\fs14}埃尔·利布勒的追随者可能会举起他们的手...{\r}
{\fs12\1c&H00FFFF&\b0\i1}El Libre's followers may yet show their hands...{\r}

158
00:17:47,955 --> 00:17:50,749
{\fs14}给我一个让男爵印象深刻的机会，叫我的马车{\r}
{\fs12\1c&H00FFFF&\b0\i1}and give me a chance to impress the Baron. Order my carriage.{\r}

159
00:17:51,083 --> 00:17:55,170
{\fs14}驱散人群，更换警卫，在街上加倍巡逻{\r}
{\fs12\1c&H00FFFF&\b0\i1}Disperse the crowd. Change the guard, and double your patrols in the street.{\r}

160
00:17:56,463 --> 00:17:58,382
{\fs14}来吧，我的美人们{\r}
{\fs12\1c&H00FFFF&\b0\i1}Come on, my popsy-wopsy-wopsies.{\r}

161
00:18:09,309 --> 00:18:13,355
{\fs14}瘟疫是吗？希望他们都能接受，格鲁达男爵先来{\r}
{\fs12\1c&H00FFFF&\b0\i1}Plague, is it? May it take all of them. Baron Gruda first.{\r}

162
00:18:13,814 --> 00:18:16,442
{\fs14}是的，如果瘟疫没弄死他们，我们也会弄死他们{\r}
{\fs12\1c&H00FFFF&\b0\i1}Aye, and if the plague don't, we will.{\r}

163
00:18:19,069 --> 00:18:21,614
{\fs14}- 你是谁？  - 跟你们一样的普通渔民{\r}
{\fs12\1c&H00FFFF&\b0\i1}- Who are you?
- Simple fisher folk like yourselves.{\r}

164
00:18:21,697 --> 00:18:25,701
{\fs14}给我们一大罐啤酒，一句友好的话，以及一个与国王战斗的机会{\r}
{\fs12\1c&H00FFFF&\b0\i1}Put in for a tankard of ale, a friendly word, and a chance to fight the King.{\r}

165
00:18:28,621 --> 00:18:30,081
{\fs14}为什么选择我们？{\r}
{\fs12\1c&H00FFFF&\b0\i1}Why choose us?{\r}

166
00:18:34,877 --> 00:18:36,671
{\fs14}你的言行举止像个战士{\r}
{\fs12\1c&H00FFFF&\b0\i1}You look and talk like a fighter.{\r}

167
00:18:37,171 --> 00:18:38,589
{\fs14}惺惺相惜吧{\r}
{\fs12\1c&H00FFFF&\b0\i1}It takes one to know one.{\r}

168
00:18:38,673 --> 00:18:41,384
{\fs14}你也许认为我们是同类，好吧，也许不是{\r}
{\fs12\1c&H00FFFF&\b0\i1}You may have us marked, all right. Maybe not.{\r}

169
00:18:41,467 --> 00:18:43,427
{\fs14}但我们并没有认同你{\r}
{\fs12\1c&H00FFFF&\b0\i1}But we haven't marked you yet.{\r}

170
00:18:43,511 --> 00:18:45,972
{\fs14}- 我们不会问任何问题   - 我们也不会{\r}
{\fs12\1c&H00FFFF&\b0\i1}- We're asking no questions.
- We are.{\r}

171
00:18:46,889 --> 00:18:49,475
{\fs14}我听到的关于埃尔·利布勒的消息，对我来说已经足够了{\r}
{\fs12\1c&H00FFFF&\b0\i1}What I've heard about El Libre is good enough for me.{\r}

172
00:18:49,559 --> 00:18:51,102
{\fs14}告诉我们怎么联系他{\r}
{\fs12\1c&H00FFFF&\b0\i1}Tell us how to contact him.{\r}

173
00:18:51,185 --> 00:18:54,731
{\fs14}像他那样的汉子肯定很乐意船上多两个全副武装的小伙子{\r}
{\fs12\1c&H00FFFF&\b0\i1}A man like him would be pleased to have two more strong-armed lads aboard.{\r}

174
00:19:02,030 --> 00:19:04,032
{\fs14}他们不轻易相信人，对吗？{\r}
{\fs12\1c&H00FFFF&\b0\i1}Not very trusting souls, are they?{\r}

175
00:19:15,752 --> 00:19:19,005
{\fs14}我想我们必须证明我们对埃尔·利布勒的高度敬仰{\r}
{\fs12\1c&H00FFFF&\b0\i1}I guess we'll have to prove our high regard for El Libre.{\r}

176
00:19:31,893 --> 00:19:34,521
{\fs14}奥约，你说出了我想说的{\r}
{\fs12\1c&H00FFFF&\b0\i1}Ojo, you took the words right out of my mouth.{\r}

177
00:19:34,604 --> 00:19:36,898
{\fs14}跟国王的手下打一架，走{\r}
{\fs12\1c&H00FFFF&\b0\i1}A brawl with the King's men. Let's go.{\r}

178
00:19:42,404 --> 00:19:46,324
{\fs14}左，右，左，原地踏步！{\r}
{\fs12\1c&H00FFFF&\b0\i1}Left, right. Left. Mark time!{\r}

179
00:19:49,244 --> 00:19:50,620
{\fs14}向右转{\r}
{\fs12\1c&H00FFFF&\b0\i1}Right turn.{\r}

180
00:19:52,581 --> 00:19:53,665
{\fs14}立定！{\r}
{\fs12\1c&H00FFFF&\b0\i1}Halt!{\r}

181
00:19:56,043 --> 00:19:59,922
{\fs14}快步走！向前！立定！向左转！{\r}
{\fs12\1c&H00FFFF&\b0\i1}Quick march! Forward! Halt! Turn!{\r}

182
00:20:09,056 --> 00:20:11,141
{\fs14}向右转！{\r}
{\fs12\1c&H00FFFF&\b0\i1}Right wheel!{\r}

183
00:20:16,271 --> 00:20:18,399
{\fs14}齐步走！{\r}
{\fs12\1c&H00FFFF&\b0\i1}March!{\r}

184
00:20:20,693 --> 00:20:21,819
{\fs14}立定！{\r}
{\fs12\1c&H00FFFF&\b0\i1}Halt!{\r}

185
00:20:23,779 --> 00:20:25,573
{\fs14}持刀敬礼！{\r}
{\fs12\1c&H00FFFF&\b0\i1}Present arms!{\r}

186
00:20:56,145 --> 00:20:57,647
{\fs14}共和国万岁！{\r}
{\fs12\1c&H00FFFF&\b0\i1}Long live the republic!{\r}

187
00:20:57,730 --> 00:20:59,607
{\fs14}叛军！抓住他们！{\r}
{\fs12\1c&H00FFFF&\b0\i1}Rebels! Get them!{\r}

188
00:21:14,998 --> 00:21:16,457
{\fs14}埃尔·利布勒万岁！{\r}
{\fs12\1c&H00FFFF&\b0\i1}Long live El Libre!{\r}

189
00:21:16,499 --> 00:21:17,917
{\fs14}追他们！{\r}
{\fs12\1c&H00FFFF&\b0\i1}After them!{\r}

190
00:22:00,502 --> 00:22:01,753
{\fs14}他们来了！{\r}
{\fs12\1c&H00FFFF&\b0\i1}There they are!{\r}

191
00:22:03,297 --> 00:22:04,756
{\fs14}别让他们跑了！{\r}
{\fs12\1c&H00FFFF&\b0\i1}Don't let them get away!{\r}

192
00:22:32,660 --> 00:22:34,620
{\fs14}伙计们！快来！{\r}
{\fs12\1c&H00FFFF&\b0\i1}Men! Come on!{\r}

193
00:23:43,440 --> 00:23:45,275
{\fs14}快点！快，到那个角落{\r}
{\fs12\1c&H00FFFF&\b0\i1}Come on! Quick, in that corner.{\r}

194
00:23:46,485 --> 00:23:47,986
{\fs14}他们来了！{\r}
{\fs12\1c&H00FFFF&\b0\i1}There they go!{\r}

195
00:23:59,915 --> 00:24:01,625
{\fs14}快点，到后面{\r}
{\fs12\1c&H00FFFF&\b0\i1}Hurry up. In back.{\r}

196
00:24:04,336 --> 00:24:05,629
{\fs14}这边走！{\r}
{\fs12\1c&H00FFFF&\b0\i1}This way!{\r}

197
00:24:10,300 --> 00:24:11,260
{\fs14}往前跑{\r}
{\fs12\1c&H00FFFF&\b0\i1}Go ahead.{\r}

198
00:24:19,727 --> 00:24:20,894
{\fs14}刺穿帆布{\r}
{\fs12\1c&H00FFFF&\b0\i1}Pierce the canvas.{\r}

199
00:24:34,742 --> 00:24:35,826
{\fs14}开火！{\r}
{\fs12\1c&H00FFFF&\b0\i1}Fire!{\r}

200
00:24:43,376 --> 00:24:44,502
{\fs14}准备，开火！{\r}
{\fs12\1c&H00FFFF&\b0\i1}Ready? Fire!{\r}

201
00:24:55,346 --> 00:24:58,307
{\fs14}抬起来！举起来！快点，举起来！开火！{\r}
{\fs12\1c&H00FFFF&\b0\i1}Pick it up! Lift it up! Come on. Lift it up! Fire!{\r}

202
00:25:02,645 --> 00:25:03,855
{\fs14}带我们走{\r}
{\fs12\1c&H00FFFF&\b0\i1}Take us away.{\r}

203
00:25:06,232 --> 00:25:08,025
{\fs14}他们逃走了！{\r}
{\fs12\1c&H00FFFF&\b0\i1}They're getting away!{\r}

204
00:25:26,294 --> 00:25:28,838
{\fs14}锁上地窖！堵住小巷！{\r}
{\fs12\1c&H00FFFF&\b0\i1}Latch the cellars! Block the alley!{\r}

205
00:25:44,646 --> 00:25:45,814
{\fs14}留神，士兵{\r}
{\fs12\1c&H00FFFF&\b0\i1}Look out. Soldiers.{\r}

206
00:25:51,987 --> 00:25:53,196
{\fs14}等一下{\r}
{\fs12\1c&H00FFFF&\b0\i1}Just a minute.{\r}

